ce:section.ce:para:
The g-C3N4-TiO2 nanosheets with {001} plane heterojunctions photocatalyst reported for the photocatalytic activities under visible light [188]. The mechanism of visible light active boron doped TiO2/g-C3N4 photocatalyst schematic representations are displayed in Fig. 23
                           . The Energy band gap values of g-C3N4 and TiO2 semiconductors are 2.4 and 3.2 eV respectively as well as edge potentials of VB and CB are −3.4 and 1.4 eV and −0.46 and 2.7 eV respectively. When g-C3N4 absorbs the photon energy greater than it Eg then electron-hole pair gets generated. The excited CB electron transfer from g-C3N4 CB to TiO2 CB as TiO2 has lower CB edge potential than the g-C3N4. The heterojunction can effectively reduce the recombination rate along that enhanced the H2 production efficiency. Also, g-C3N4-TiO2 photocatalyst for H2 production reported by Mohammad et al., [196]. However, g-C3N4 alone showed low activity, while the addition of TiO2 improved the H2 production by forming the heterojunction interface between the two semiconductor materials. In this heterojunction interface, the utilization of solar light is more effective than in the single semiconductor photocatalyst alone, and this interface is used for either photocatalytic oxidation or reduction process (Fig. 24
                           ).
